# everything-evenhub skills (Cursor adaptation)

Even Realities ships an official AI skill set for G2 development: [everything-evenhub](https://github.com/even-realities/everything-evenhub). It targets Claude Code and Codex CLI plugins ([docs](https://hub.evenrealities.com/docs/AI-tooling/claude-code)). **Cursor cannot install Claude plugins directly**, but agents should consult the upstream skill files when relevant.

## Upstream skill location

```
https://github.com/even-realities/everything-evenhub/tree/main/plugins/everything-evenhub/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md
```

Fetch or read the matching `SKILL.md` before implementing the topic below. Do not guess SDK behavior when a skill exists.

## Skill → task mapping

| Task | Consult skill |
|------|----------------|
| Scaffold blank app | `quickstart` |
| Scaffold from template | `template` |
| Package / publish `.ehpk` | `build-and-deploy`, `cli-reference` |
| G2 display / containers | `glasses-ui`, `design-guidelines` |
| Touchpad + R1 input | `handle-input` |
| Audio, IMU, device info | `device-features` |
| Background state persistence | `background-state` |
| Simulator workflow | `test-with-simulator` |
| Simulator HTTP automation | `simulator-automation` |
| Text measurement / pagination | `font-measurement` |
| SDK API lookup | `sdk-reference` |

## This repo vs upstream skills

- This project already implements patterns from `minimal` template + `handle-input` event routing.
- Prefer **installed SDK types** (`node_modules/@evenrealities/even_hub_sdk/dist/index.d.ts`) over skill prose when they conflict.
- Hermes HTTP integration is **not** covered by everything-evenhub; follow `AGENTS.md` roadmap and `docs/security.md`.

## Optional: install upstream for Claude Code users

```bash
/plugin marketplace add even-realities/everything-evenhub
/plugin install everything-evenhub
```

Cursor users rely on this rule + `docs/ai-tooling.md` instead.
